, den die Jugendlichen beim gemeinsamen Schreiben kreieren, macht das innovative Potenzial erkennbar, welches die (Inter-)Medialisierung des Alltags sowie die Migrationsbewegungen für die Sprache und das Erzählen bereithalten.  aThis volume focuses on the form of literary writing that is emerging from the lifeworld of young people. The »style« which is becoming increasingly evident in this context is innovative, and sometimes even avant-garde.  afunded by Swiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEthnology. Social and cultural anthropology. 0aGerman languagexStyle. 0aYoung adult literature, GermanxAuthorship. 0aYouth in literature. 4aAgency. 4aAlltagssprache. 4aBildung. 4aBildungsungleichheit. 4aIntermedialität. 4aJugend. 4aKultur. 4aKulturanthropologie. 4aLebenswelt. 4aLiteratur. 4aMedien. 4aMigration. 4aMigrationsgesellschaft. 4aMündlichkeit. 4aSchreiben. 4aSozialarbeit. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAgency.  aCultural Anthropology.  aCulture.  aEducation.  aEducational Inequality.  aIntermediality.  aLifeworld.  aLiterature.  aMedia.  aMigration Society.  aMigration.  aOral Language.  aSocial Work.  aWriting.  aYouth.2 aSwiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z97831107010120 cprintz978383763346740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839433461zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://